
Step 1: Identify catch blocks that create and throw new exceptions without including the original exception:

Java
catch (Exception e) { throw new OtherException("msg"); }
Step 2: Modify to pass the original exception as the cause:

Java
throw new OtherException("msg", e);
Step 3: If the custom exception class lacks a constructor with cause:

Add either a (String, Throwable) or (Throwable) constructor
